ArcheoShape - Software tools for archeological pieces modeling

Licensing information
_____________________

The source code and compilation files of the ArcheoShape project are available under the terms of the MIT license (see LICENSE_MIT file). The "scr" folder contains all the source code of this repository whereas the folder "vs" has the compilation files.

Mesh files and project resources (images, preprocesed data and configuration files) are protected by the terms of the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International Public License (see LICENSE_CC_BY-NC_4.0 file). The mesh files are in the "models" folder and the rest of the resources are in the "resources" folder.

This repository also contains a compiled version of the project code ("bin" path). The executable runs on Windows, and requires some QT libraries which are distributed with the executable under the terms of the GNU Lesser General Public License v.3. The executable contains the license file for QT modules. 

